      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_CRIS_PreProcessMiscellaneousChargeCode050Updates",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to update records in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CrisNationalGridWest.UploadAccountBillingAdjustmentCrisGas",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table. It specifically addresses adjustments related to a \"Code 050\" charge, which is a type of miscellaneous charge. The procedure ensures that any null values in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Code050Amount",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " column are set to zero and then updates this column with the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "MiscellaneousChargeAmount",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " where the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "MiscellaneousChargeType",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is '050'. It subsequently adjusts several financial fields by subtracting the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Code050Amount",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "."
        }
